Here's the recommended approach using **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** source generators:

**ViewModel â€” `ProductDetailViewModel.cs`**

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        // Replace with your actual data service call
        var product = await FetchProductAsync();
        Name = product.Name;
        Price = product.Price;
        IsAvailable = product.IsAvailable;
    }

    private async Task<(string Name, decimal Price, bool IsAvailable)> FetchProductAsync()
    {
        await Task.Delay(500); // simulate network
        return ("Widget Pro", 29.99m, true);
    }
}
```

The source generator creates public `Name`, `Price`, `IsAvailable` properties (with `PropertyChanged` notifications) and a `LoadCommand` â€” all automatically.

**XAML page â€” `ProductDetailPage.xaml`**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailViewModel"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ProductDetailPage">

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="16" Spacing="12">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="24" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='Price: {0:C2}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='In Stock: {0}'}" />
        <Button Text="Load Product"
                Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
        <!-- LoadCommand auto-disables the button while running -->
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Code-behind (with DI)**

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailPage(ProductDetailViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- `[ObservableProperty]` generates the public property + `PropertyChanged` raise.
- `[RelayCommand]` on `LoadAsync` generates `LoadCommand` which auto-disables while executing.
- `x:DataType` enables **compiled bindings** (8â€“20Ă— faster, AOT-safe).
- Add `<WarningsAsErrors>XC0022;XC0025</WarningsAsErrors>` to your `.csproj` to catch binding errors at build time.
- Requires NuGet package **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** (â‰Ą 8.0).
